# Workspace Overview

This file describes workspace-level entry points and routing. For a child project's internal architecture, business methods, utilities, and project rules, read that child skill's `references/project-spec.md` and `references/project-overview.md`.

## Projects

{{range .Projects}}
- `{{.ID}}`: `{{.Path}}`, type `{{.Type}}`, language `{{.Language}}`
  - Skill: `{{.Path}}/.agents/skills/{{.SkillName}}/SKILL.md` or `{{.Path}}/.claude/skills/{{.SkillName}}/SKILL.md`
  - Project spec: `{{.Path}}/.agents/skills/{{.SkillName}}/references/project-spec.md` or `{{.Path}}/.claude/skills/{{.SkillName}}/references/project-spec.md`
{{else}}
- No child projects configured.
{{end}}

{{if .Shared}}
## Shared Paths

{{range .Shared}}
- `{{.Path}}`{{if .Description}} - {{.Description}}{{end}}
  - After changes, check every child project that imports, packages, or generates this shared content.
{{end}}
{{end}}

{{if .Contracts}}
## Contract Paths

{{range .Contracts}}
- `{{.Path}}`{{if .Description}} - {{.Description}}{{end}}
  - After changes, check producers, consumers, generated clients, server handlers, middleware adapters, and tests.
{{end}}
{{end}}

{{if .Infra}}
## Infra Paths

{{range .Infra}}
- `{{.Path}}`{{if .Description}} - {{.Description}}{{end}}
  - After changes, check child projects affected by deployment targets, environment variables, gateway rules, or middleware config.
{{end}}
{{end}}

## Routing Table

| Path Pattern | Child Project | What To Read |
| --- | --- | --- |
{{range .Projects}}
| `{{.Path}}/**` | `{{.ID}}` | child `SKILL.md` and `references/project-spec.md` |
{{end}}
{{if .Contracts}}
| `contracts/**` or configured contract paths | related producers and consumers | all contract-affected child project skills |
{{end}}
{{if .Shared}}
| `shared/**` or configured shared paths | all consumers | all child skills that import shared content |
{{end}}
{{if .Infra}}
| `infra/**` or configured infra paths | deployment-affected projects | runtime service, middleware, and deployment target skills |
{{end}}
